    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any interaction that, when unopposed, will change the motion of an object; force may be an agency or influence (as a push or pull) that, if applied to a free body, results chiefly in an acceleration of the body and sometimes in elastic deformation and other effects. Equations differ in ancient, pre-Newtonian, and Newtonian understandings of force.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
